records.uuResumeText:
PRASHANTH REDDY GUDALA
Email: prashanthgudala843@gmail.com | Phone: +1-502-701-2010 | LinkedIn


Salesforce Lead | 9x Salesforce Certified | 8.5+ Years of Experience

Professional Summary
Results-driven Salesforce Lead with 8.5 years of experience in Apex development (Controllers,
Batch, Scheduled Apex), LWC/Aura component development, REST/SOAP integrations, and
Visualforce Pages. Skilled in Salesforce Sales, Service, and Experience Clouds with expertise in
creating workflows, triggers, technical documentation, mentoring developers on best practices
and earning client recognition through consistent delivery of business value.

Core Competencies
•   Salesforce Platforms: Sales Cloud, Service Cloud, CPQ, Experience Cloud, Data cloud,
    Agentforce
•   Programming & Customization: Apex (Batch, Scheduled Apex, Triggers, Queueable, REST
    API), LWC, Aura, Visualforce, SOQL, SOSL.
•   Integrations: RESTful APIs, SOAP APIs, External System Integrations.
•   DevOps & Tools: Jenkins, GitHub, ANT, VS Code, Data Loader, Workbench, Informatica Cloud
•   Architecture & Admin: Security, Profiles, Roles, Flows, Workflows, Approvals, Reporting &
    Dashboards
•   Other Skills: Agile/Scrum, Requirement Gathering, Solution Design, Project Management,
    Debugging, Testing, Maintenance, Technical Documentation, Talent Acquisition

Certifications
•   Developer/Admin: Salesforce Certified Platform Developer I, Salesforce Certified
    Administrator
•   Agent Force: Salesforce Certified AI Associate
•   Cloud: Sales Cloud Consultant, Service Cloud Consultant, Platform App Builder
•   Architect: Salesforce Certified Sharing & Visibility Architect, Salesforce Certified Data
    Architect, Salesforce Certified Application Architect

Professional Experience

Verizon – Dallas, USA

Salesforce Lead | Mar 2022 – Present
• Led Lightning migration initiatives, driving user adoption and improving order management
    efficiency.
•   Configured Salesforce CPQ (Product Rules, Price Rules, QLE, Quote Calculator Plugin),
    enabling accurate quoting and pricing automation.
•   Designed and deployed customer portals using LWC and Aura, improving customer
    experience.
•   Designed and implemented Data Cloud integrations to unify customer data from multiple
    sources (Sales Cloud, Service Cloud, external databases), creating a single source of truth for
    360° customer view.
•   Built segmentation rules and calculated insights in Data Cloud, enabling targeted campaigns
    and improved customer engagement.
•   Configured data streams, data lake objects, identity resolution rules, and harmonization for
    enterprise clients.
•   Performed Apex code reviews, ensuring adherence to best practices.
•   Created complex workflows, triggers, and Scheduled Apex jobs to automate processes.
•   Partnered with DevOps team to optimize CI/CD pipelines in Jenkins, reducing release errors
    and improving deployment speed.
•   Delivered solutions using Apex triggers, batch jobs, and configuration enhancements
    (reports, validations, metadata).
•   Integrated Salesforce with external applications using RESTful and SOAP APIs.
•   Produced technical documentation and provided technical solutions to business teams.
•   Mentored team members on deployments, test automation, and best practices.
•   Supported Windows server monitoring and collaborated cross-functionally to ensure system
    health.

Salesforce – Hyderabad, India

Proactive Monitoring Engineer | Oct 2019 – Dec 2021
• Managed customer cases, delivered resolutions, and performed root cause analysis for
   SEV1/SEV2 incidents.
• Conducted annual technical health checks for enterprise Salesforce orgs, improving system
   reliability.
• Performed debugging, installation, and testing of Salesforce applications for enterprise
   customers.
• Reviewed data and provided technical recommendations to business stakeholders.
• Collaborated on proof-of-concept solutions for strategic accounts like Intuit.
• Maintained 95%+ QA scores and achieved zero-miss case transactions, ensuring consistent
   client satisfaction.

Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) – Hyderabad, India

Salesforce Developer | Jul 2016 – Jun 2019
Client: Dupont
•   Built a 360° Customer Data view in Service Cloud, integrating with multiple enterprise
    applications (iPASS, CDB, EDP, SOO).
•   Developed customized Service Cloud applications (case management, service contracts,
    contact/account management).
•   Developed Visualforce Pages and customized Service Cloud applications.
•   Created Apex Controllers and scheduled jobs for automation.
•   Built Aura components to enhance user experience.
•   Automated user access management, reducing manual overhead for account provisioning.
•   Implemented Lightning pages/components, Apex triggers, and batch jobs following best
    practices.
•   Contributed to release management using ANT and Git and participated in requirement
    analysis and solution design.
•   Mentored junior engineers, upskilling 3 into independent leads, which improved delivery
    capacity.

Awards & Recognition
•   Customer Hero Award (2020) – Recognized for exceptional client support.
•   Best Performer – Salesforce (2021)
•   On-the-Spot Award (2019) – Outstanding contributions at Salesforce.
•   Star Team Award (2017 & 2018), Best Performer Award (2018) – TCS.

Education
Bachelor of Technology (B.Tech) – JNTU Hyderabad, 2016
